teacher_info.teaching_style:
My teaching method: 
- We define your level; 
- You get the materials prepared for your level and interests; 
- During the lessons, we TALK and SHARE ideas; 
- We learn grammar step by step, I can make things clear to YOU; 
- I LOVE discussing grammar and culture, so if that interests you - try me!  
- During the first lesson (or the trial lesson), we will pick a structured course for you to make sure you feel comfortable and interested during the sessions! 
- You get the homework for almost every lesson.
- You get feedback after every lesson.
- We review what you have learned so you won't forget the new things we studied together.

teacher_info.introduction:
Hello! My name is Evgeny (Eugene), I am from Russia, Moscow. I've graduated from Moscow State Linguistic University, German Faculty, Theology Department. While studying there I was learning five languages: English and German (which I speak fluently and teach at the university), Ancient Greek, Latin and Church-Slavonic. Now I'am starting to learn Japanese and French, so believe me, I know what it's like to learn a language. I am also a theologian, a practicing Orthodox Christian. 

People usually say I am patient, open-minded, kind and optimistic. I love having deep, inspiring conversations, love learning from people and listening to their stories. I think that every human live is unique, precious and truly awesome in the original sense of this word — inspiring awe. 

I offer speaking practice in Russian (all levels), English and German (up to C1 level). Having scheduled a session with me, please, write me a message with your goals and interests. I am flexible and will adapt my teaching strategy to your needs. 

My general idea of a speaking practice session is as follows: 
- we choose a topic to discuss; 
- I pick out some interesting related material and send it to you for consideration. You can make your own suggestions; 
- I send you questions and (optionally) some necessary words/expressions related to the chosen material; 
- the questions serve us as a starting point for a conversation during the session.

**Cancellation / Connection Problem Policy - Lessons can only be rescheduled more than 24 hours before the scheduled start. Otherwise, if you are not able to meet at the last minute for any reason, including a technical problem, I expect to be paid for the lesson.

**Late Policy - I will wait no longer than 10 minutes after the scheduled start of class, at which point I consider the student 'absent' and expect to receive the payment.
